    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-20T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="646"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">615.6231/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-20T13:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 20, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Referring to the Legation’s despatches Nos. 731 and 515 of July 17, 1937 and
                    November 21, 1938 respectively.<note n="10" xml:id="d646fn10">Neither
                        printed.</note> The Foreign Minister informed me today that the German
                    Government has made representations to the Honduran Government with respect to
                    extending Honduras’ commercial treaty with Germany<note n="11" xml:id="d646fn11"
                        >Signed March 4, 1926, Martens, <hi rend="italic">Nouveau Recueil Général de
                            Traités</hi>, tome <hi rend="smallcaps">cxxii</hi>, p. 560.</note> for
                    one year. Treaty expires on December 21. The Government of Honduras is holding
                    matter in abeyance until attitude of the United States Government is known.
                    Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Erwin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
